<TITLE> Romans to build Shaheed Minar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 19 (bdnews24.com)--Italy has donated a prime piece of land in the heart of Rome to construct a Shaheed Minar, a foreign ministry official said. "After a lot of effort the Italians have given us a site near our embassy to construct a permanent Shaheed Minar," the official in Dhaka said. "So for the first time we are organising commemoration with a makeshift Minar in a big way," an embassy official in Rome said. The official in Rome, speaking on condition that he not be named, said the Italy-based Bangladeshi opposition activists had been invited to the Ekushey programmes on Sunday. "But they announced a parallel programme." Since the UN recognised it as International Mother Language Day in memory of the 1952 Language Movement martyrs in Dhaka, the Feb 21 is now marked in major capitals. The ancient Rome will add to an impressive list of world cities that host such a memorial in honour of those who fought and died trying to protect Bangla as mother tong
